.TH CHMOD 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chmod \- change file mode bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chmod
.I MODE FILE
.SH DESCRIPTION
Change the mode (permissions) of
.IR FILE
to
.IR MODE .
.PP
.I MODE
is specified as an octal number representing the permission bits:
.IP \(bu 3
First digit: user permissions
.IP \(bu
Second digit: group permissions
.IP \(bu
Third digit: other permissions
.PP
Each digit is the sum of:
.IP \(bu 3
4 = read
.IP \(bu
2 = write
.IP \(bu
1 = execute
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B chmod 755 script.sh
Set permissions to rwxr-xr-x (owner can read/write/execute,
others can read/execute).
.TP
.B chmod 644 file.txt
Set permissions to rw-r--r-- (owner can read/write,
others can only read).
.TP
.B chmod 777 shared
Give everyone full permissions (rwxrwxrwx).
.SH NOTES
The Nightingale chmod only supports numeric (octal) modes,
not symbolic modes like
.B u+x
or
.BR a=rw .
